      "Pollution dome installed over 60 inch casing"
    ],
    "summary": "On July 25, 2018, during plug and abandon operations at Ship Shoal Block 114 well #44, the 9.625 inch bent casing ruptured while being uprighted to vertical position using a 60 inch casing as a lever arm and Vibro Hammer. The rupture released approximately 56 gallons of hydrocarbons into the Gulf of Mexico. The casing parted at the bend location and rose approximately 37 inches, causing oil and water to spout 20-30 feet into the air for approximately 30 seconds.",
